notifyHalt() is defied (in the refactored version) in the parent of class ReteWorkingMemory which is StatefulKnowledgeSessionImpl
the body of notifyHalt() in StatefulKnowledgeSessionImpl we have: propagationList.notifyHalt();
knowing that InternalAgenda has no type relation with PropagationList => it is FP

purity.purityComment:
Overlapped refactoring - can be identical by undoing the overlapped refactoring
 Severe changes

refactorings.description: Move Attribute private msgLog : Log from class org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.pruning.LogPruning to private msgLog : Log from class org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.checkpoint.CheckPointerImpl
refactorings.comment:
There are different possibilities: The old class has become an interface and a new class implementing the interface is created.

1) The old class has become an interface and a new class implementing the interface is created. The attribute is pushed down to this new class

2) The new interface is extracted from the existing class (something like extract super class)

3) The old class is renamed to the new class and an interface with the same name as the old class is created and the old class is now implementing it

refactorings.comment:
channel appears now in two new classes, LogEntryCursor and Maker. Both of them are now used in the source class, and the old channel (coming from the ctor's param) is passed to both of them

Davood & Laleh: The places where channel is used in PhysicalTransactionCursor do not relate to the places where Marker is used in the new version
